In mathematics, the '''hyperkähler quotient''' of a [[hyperkähler manifold]] acted on by a [[Group (mathematics)|group]] ''G'' is the quotient of a fiber of the hyperkähler moment map ''M''→'''R'''<sup>3</sup>⊗''g''* over a ''G''-fixed point (or more generally a ''G''-orbit) by the action of ''G''. It was introduced by {{harvs|txt | last4=Roček | first4=M. | last3=Lindström | first3=U. | last2=Karlhede | first2=A. | last1=Hitchin | first1=N. J. | title=Hyper-Kähler metrics and supersymmetry | url=http://projecteuclid.org/getRecord?id=euclid.cmp/1104116624 |mr=877637 | year=1987 | journal=Communications in Mathematical Physics | issn=0010-3616 | volume=108 | issue=4 | pages=535–589}}. It is a hyperkähler analogue of the [[Kähler quotient]].

