{{Redirect|Pors|the Norwegian football club|Pors Grenland}}

'''PORS''' stands for Plus One Recall Store. It is a problem used in [[evolutionary computation]] and [[genetic programming]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=kz0rofjQrwYC&lpg=PA215&ots=zECFAmBXB1&dq=PORS%20language&pg=PA215#v=onepage&q=PORS%20language&f=false 8.2 The PORS Language], Page 215, Evolutionary Computation for Modeling And Optimization - Daniel Ashlock - Google Books</ref>

The PORS language consists of two terminal nodes (1 and recall), one unary operation (store) and one binary operation (plus) that together make up a [[parse tree]] that calculates a number.

